Citation.sAuthor: Alkhaldi, K. H. A. E.[Khaled H. A. E.]
Citation.sTitle: Comparative study of physical properties of binary mixtures of halogen free ionic liquids with alcohols
Citation.sAbstract: Densities, refractive indices and speeds of sound along with their excess or deviation properties for both 1,3-dimethylimidazolium methylsulfate ([dmim][MeSO4]) and 1-ethyl-3-methylimidazolium methylsulfate ([emim][MeSO4]) with 1-propanol, 1-butanol and 1-pentanol over the entire range of mole fraction are reported at temperatures ranging from 298.15 K to 313.15 K and atmospheric pressure. Isentropic and excess isentropic compressibilities for both ionic liquids with 1-alcohols were calculated from the experimental results. Excess and deviation properties were further correlated using the Redlich-Kister polynomial. The measured speeds of sound were compared to the values obtained from Schaaffs collision factor theory, Jacobson s intermolecular free length theory of solutions and Nomoto s relation. In addition, the experimentally obtained refractive indices were compared to the calculated values using Lorentz-Lorenz, Dale-Gladstone and Eykman mixing rules.
